The paper is about recurrent neural networks and their performance on various tasks, including speech recognition. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.SD (Sound), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Among these, cs.LG and cs.NE are the most likely categories, as the paper focuses on the performance of neural networks and their learning capabilities. The paper also mentions speech recognition, which falls under cs.CL and cs.SD, and the use of complex-valued operators, which is relevant to cs.AI.
